SR:
To reproduce the issue, you can use the following code:
1. Create an ImageData instance with a color depth that is not supported, like:
   ImageData data = new ImageData(10, 10, 32, new PaletteData(0xff0000, 0x00ff00, 0x0000ff));
2. Create an Image using the ImageData and a Device instance:
   Image image = new Image(Display.getDefault(), data);
3. Observe that the constructor may throw an org.eclipse.swt.SWTException: Unsupported color depth.
